2 unit(s) Egg
100 g Bacon Strips
2 unit(s) Brioche Bun
2 tbsp Maple Syrup
1 unit(s) Gala Apple
2 g Warming Spice Blend
237 mL Cream
2 tbsp Brown Sugar
0.13 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Peel, core, then cut apple into 1/4-inch pieces.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp butter, then apples. Cook, stirring often, until tender-crisp, 4-5 min.
Meanwhile, cut brioche into 1-inch pieces.

Whisk together eggs, brown sugar, Pumpkin Pie Spice Mix, cream and 1/8 tsp salt in a large bowl.
Add brioche and apples to egg mixture. Stir to coat until liquid is absorbed.
Add mixture to a greased 8x8-inch baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake in the middle of the oven until puffed and golden-brown, 38-40 min. (NOTE: Remove the foil in the last 5 min of baking.)

Meanwhile, arrange bacon on a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Bake in the bottom of the oven until crispy and cooked through, 12-15 min.**

Allow apple french toast bake to cool slightly before serving, 3-5 min.
Serve with maple syrup and bacon on the side.